2. STEP 1 — Install Zabbix Repository
Add the official Zabbix 4.0 repository for CentOS 7:

# Install Zabbix repository
rpm -ivh https://repo.zabbix.com/zabbix/4.0/rhel/7/x86_64/zabbix-release-4.0-1.el7.noarch.rpm

# Clean and update yum cache
yum clean all
yum makecache

3. STEP 2 — Install Zabbix Server, Frontend & Agent
# Install Zabbix server with MySQL support, web frontend, and agent
yum install -y zabbix-server-mysql zabbix-web-mysql zabbix-agent

# Install MariaDB server
yum install -y mariadb-server mariadb

# Start and enable MariaDB
systemctl start mariadb
systemctl enable mariadb

4. STEP 3 — MariaDB Database Setup
As seen in Screenshot 1, log into MariaDB as root and create the Zabbix database:

# Secure MariaDB installation first
mysql_secure_installation

# Login to MariaDB (as shown in screenshot)
mysql -u root -p

Inside MariaDB shell:
-- Create Zabbix database
CREATE DATABASE zabbix CHARACTER SET utf8 COLLATE utf8_bin;

-- Create Zabbix user and grant privileges
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON zabbix.* TO zabbix@localhost IDENTIFIED BY 'your_password';

-- Apply privileges
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

-- Exit MariaDB
EXIT;

Import Zabbix schema:
# Import initial schema and data
zcat /usr/share/doc/zabbix-server-mysql*/create.sql.gz | mysql -uzabbix -p zabbix

5. STEP 4 — Configure Zabbix Server
Edit the main Zabbix server configuration file:

vi /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server.conf

Key settings to configure in zabbix_server.conf:

Parameter	Value / Setting
DBHost	localhost
DBName	zabbix
DBUser	zabbix
DBPassword	your_password
ListenPort	10051
LogFile	/var/log/zabbix/zabbix_server.log
PidFile	/var/run/zabbix/zabbix_server.pid
SocketDir	/var/run/zabbix
SNMPTrapperFile	/var/log/snmptrap/snmptrap.log
Timeout	4
AlertScriptsPath	/usr/lib/zabbix/alertscripts
ExternalScripts	/usr/lib/zabbix/externalscripts

Full /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server.conf snippet:
# --- /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server.conf ---
LogFile=/var/log/zabbix/zabbix_server.log
LogFileSize=0
PidFile=/var/run/zabbix/zabbix_server.pid
SocketDir=/var/run/zabbix
DBHost=localhost
DBName=zabbix
DBUser=zabbix
DBPassword=your_password
SNMPTrapperFile=/var/log/snmptrap/snmptrap.log
Timeout=4
AlertScriptsPath=/usr/lib/zabbix/alertscripts
ExternalScripts=/usr/lib/zabbix/externalscripts
LogSlowQueries=3000

6. STEP 5 — Configure PHP for Zabbix Frontend
Edit Apache PHP configuration for Zabbix:

vi /etc/httpd/conf.d/zabbix.conf

Contents of /etc/httpd/conf.d/zabbix.conf:
Alias /zabbix /usr/share/zabbix

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix">
    Options FollowSymLinks
    AllowOverride None
    Require all granted

    <IfModule mod_php5.c>
        php_value max_execution_time 300
        php_value memory_limit 128M
        php_value post_max_size 16M
        php_value upload_max_filesize 2M
        php_value max_input_time 300
        php_value max_input_vars 10000
        php_value always_populate_raw_post_data -1
        php_value date.timezone Asia/Kolkata
    </IfModule>
</Directory>

📝 NOTE: Set date.timezone to your local timezone (e.g., Asia/Kolkata for India, America/New_York for US East)

7. STEP 6 — Start & Enable Services
# Start Zabbix server
systemctl start zabbix-server
systemctl enable zabbix-server

# Start Zabbix agent
systemctl start zabbix-agent
systemctl enable zabbix-agent

# Start Apache
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd

# Verify all services are running
systemctl status zabbix-server
systemctl status zabbix-agent
systemctl status httpd
systemctl status mariadb

8. STEP 7 — Firewall Configuration
# Open Zabbix server port
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=10051/tcp

# Open Zabbix agent port
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=10050/tcp

# Open HTTP port
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http

# Reload firewall
firewall-cmd --reload

# Verify open ports
firewall-cmd --list-all

9. STEP 8 — SELinux Configuration
# Allow Zabbix to connect to DB
setsebool -P httpd_can_network_connect 1
setsebool -P httpd_can_connect_zabbix 1

# Or temporarily disable SELinux (not recommended for prod)
setenforce 0

# Check SELinux status
sestatus

